get /catalog/data/app_events/count
Event count for application (catalogDataAppEventsCountGet)
Gets the event count for the application

Query parameters

since (optional)
Query Parameter — Time from which the event count needs to be returned. If the value is not provided, returns the event count from user's last read point. format: int64
until (optional)
Query Parameter — Time until which the event count needs to be returned. If the value is not provided, returns the event count until the current time. format: int64
objectName (optional)
Query Parameter — Filter changes on object name.
changeType (optional)
Query Parameter — Filter changes on change types.
resourceName (optional)
Query Parameter — Filter events by resource.
jobId (optional)
Query Parameter — Filter events by job id.

Return type

EventsCountResponse

Example data

Content-Type: application/json
{
  "count" : 123456789,
  "until" : 123456789,
  "since" : 123456789
}

get /catalog/data/app_events
Events for the application (catalogDataAppEventsGet)
Gets the events for the application

Query parameters

since (optional)
Query Parameter — Time from which the events needs to be returned. If the value is not provided, assumed value is user's last read point. format: int64
until (optional)
Query Parameter — Time until which the events needs to be returned. If the value is not provided, assumed value is current time. format: int64
objectName (optional)
Query Parameter — Filter events by object name.
changeType (optional)
Query Parameter — Filter events by change types.
resourceName (optional)
Query Parameter — Filter events by resource.
jobId (optional)
Query Parameter — Filter events by job id.
pageSize (optional)
Query Parameter — Results per page default: 20
offset (optional)
Query Parameter — Starting from result default: 0

get /catalog/data/search
Catalog search (catalogDataSearchGet)
Search the catalog for search hits

Query parameters

q (optional)
Query Parameter — Search query to match objects. Return order undefined. [Lucene Query Syntax](https://lucene.apache.org/core/2_9_4/queryparsersyntax.html)
basicQuery (optional)
Query Parameter — EDC query string format. See documentation for details.
fq (optional)
Query Parameter — Filter queries to apply on top of q. Useful for applying facets.
facet (optional)
Query Parameter — If facets should be returned with this query. default: false
defaultFacets (optional)
Query Parameter — If faceting is enabled, true if pre-defined default facets should be included default: true
facetId (optional)
Query Parameter — If faceting is enabled, list of pre-defined facet ids to facet on.
queryFacetJson (optional)
Query Parameter — If faceting is enabled, user can specify query facet in JSON format to create on the fly facet.
fieldFacetJson (optional)
Query Parameter — If faceting is enabled, user can specify field facet in JSON format to create on the fly facet.
sliderFacetJson (optional)
Query Parameter — If faceting is enabled, user can specify slider facet in JSON format to create on the fly facet.
rootTo (optional)
Query Parameter — Results can be joined to either their root resource or data set
relatedId (optional)
Query Parameter — Results can be joined to objects that are related to the given id(s)
highlight (optional)
Query Parameter — True if highlighting should be performed on results default: false
offset (optional)
Query Parameter — Starting from result default: 0
pageSize (optional)
Query Parameter — Results per page default: 20
sort (optional)
Query Parameter — Field on which results to be sorted from search. Default is relevance(score). Usage core.name_sort asc/desc
cursor (optional)
Query Parameter — As an alternative to offset, this can provide faster paginated results when deep paging
shards (optional)
Query Parameter — Advanced option. List of search shards to query. By default all shards are queried.
tabId (optional)
Query Parameter — Apply filters for the given tab
fl (optional)
Query Parameter — The fl parameter limits the information included in a query response to a specified list of fields.
qf (optional)
Query Parameter — The qf parameter specifies the fields in the index on which to perform the query. The parameter should only reference the index attributes having index="true" in the view model. Searching on non-indexed attributes will returns no hits.
enableLegacySearch (optional)
Query Parameter — The parameter is deprecated! This is applicable to native query only. True if to default search on legacy fields which splits on whitespace, lower-case and prefix match. default: false
disableSemanticSearch (optional)
Query Parameter — True if semantic search (i.e. auto filtering) should be disabled. default: false
includeRefObjects (optional)
Query Parameter — Whether to include reference objects or not. default: false

Query Parameter — Filter queries to apply on top of q. Useful for applying facets.

Query Parameter — If faceting is enabled, list of pre-defined facet ids to facet on.

pageSize (optional)
